cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on pun detection and location in English. Additionally, the use of a new tagging scheme to capture structural information suggests a focus on computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a machine learning approach to pun detection and location. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper employs a sequence labeling perspective and proposes a model for pun detection and location. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper may use neural networks for its proposed model. 

Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely sub-category as the paper may discuss the social and cultural implications of puns in English language use.
